<br>
The bear did not give up, though.  He kept coming towards her, growling full force, bearing his teeth, and thrashing his claws in her direction.  She rolled her head down, in defense, threatening to attack him with her black pearl horn.  Elyren spread her large black wings open, stretching each feather which adorned the two.  Her black main and tail twitched in the forest breeze and had lost it's lively shine.  Instead, it was tangled from distress.<br>
<br>
She dug her hoof into the ground, grinding dirt backwards in a threatening manner.  She snorted at him as he lashed at her.  His claws ripped the raven fur and flesh on her neck.  She threw her head up, attempting to slash him with her horn, piercingly neighing in agony.  A deep crimson seeped threw her ebony fur as she staggered away from the bear.  She gasped for breath as he started to come at her again.<br>
<br>
