<br>
Acorna gasped and galloped as fast as she could to the pegasi aid. Her bow cocked and ready she let an arrow fly, but in her distress the arrow missed and imbedded its furry into the tree behind the bear. Acorna snarled and aimed this time. The arrow flew and cut deep into the bears side. Not enough, Thought Acorna as she aimed another arrow with her bow. She fired the arrow and hit the bear again. This time square in the head. The bear toppled over onto its side. Blood pouring from his wounds and its life slowly fading away.<br>
<br>
Acorna sighed and walked over to the bear. She pulled the arrows out of the dead corps. Quickly cleaning them off she put them back in her quiver. Turning to Elyren she smiled and said, &quot;I have been after this bear for along time.&quot; <br>
<br>
She saw that the pegasi was hurt and walked over to it. Gently she laid her hand on Elyren's back. Using all her magic slowly the hand started to glow and slowly Elyren's wound was healing. <p>+~+~Acorna~+~+<br>
-The Golden Hind<br>
